@AGENTS.md

## Claude Code specifics

The contract above (from `AGENTS.md`) is authoritative. A few Claude-only notes:

- **File-level invariants are enforced by `.claude/settings.local.json`.** Its
  permission deny-list blocks edits to `.decanter.json` and `*.remote.js`, reads/edits
  of `.env`, and `push --force`. If an `Edit`/`Write` is blocked, it broke a hard rule —
  fix the edit, don't route around the guard. The content-level invariants (jsCode
  placeholder integrity, the `@ts-n8n` marker) are the CLI's wall at `push`/`check`.
- **After editing a node source (`.ts`/`.js`), a PostToolUse hook runs
  `n8n-decanter check`** (layout compliance + typecheck) via `.claude/hooks/verify.mjs`
  and feeds any failure back to you. Treat a failure as a blocker to finishing the task.
  The hook is a quiet no-op until the CLI is on your PATH (install it globally or
  `npm link` it) — until then run `n8n-decanter check` / `n8n-decanter node run` yourself.
- **Renames happen in n8n, then `pull` reconciles** (see "Renaming a node" in
  AGENTS.md). For multi-node renames, pull after each MCP rename so nothing is
  left half-updated — and remember `.ts` sources keep their `$('…')` refs
  until you update them by hand.
- **`push --force` is blocked from the agent by design.** It overrides the drift guard;
  if it is genuinely needed, ask the user to run it themselves in the terminal.
